      • autoIncrement

        public boolean autoIncrement
        The field that indicates whether the value in this column is a number that is incremented automatically, which makes the value read-only. true means that the value in this column is automatically numbered; false means that it is not.

        The field that indicates whether the value in this column is nullable. The possible values are the ResultSet constants columnNoNulls, columnNullable, and columnNullableUnknown.

      • signed

        The field that indicates whether the value in this column is a signed number. true means that it is; false that it is not.

      • colPrecision

        public int colPrecision
        The field that holds the precision of the value in this column. For number types, the precision is the total number of decimal digits; for character types, it is the maximum number of characters; for binary types, it is the maximum length in bytes.

      • colScale

        public int colScale
        The field that holds the scale (number of digits to the right of the decimal point) of the value in this column.

      • tableName

        public String tableName
        The field that holds the name of the table from which this column was derived. This value may be the empty string if there is no table name, such as when this column is produced by a join.

      • catName

        public String catName
        The field that holds the catalog name for the table from which this column was derived. If the DBMS does not support catalogs, the value may be the empty string.
